title: Led Zeppelin 1969.10.10 - Paris
description:
Yeah, well, right then.  On we go.  A nice break in Chicago, but it&#039;s a long way to Paris, so we&#039;d better get started.  

Been sitting on this one for a while, not sure if it&#039;s still relevant or not but it&#039;s the next in the series and I&#039;m sure with all the discussion about it, there&#039;ll be some folks who didn&#039;t get it when it came around.  What is it, you say?  Paris 10.10.69, the FM broadcast from 11.07.07.  You&#039;ll ask me, someone will I&#039;m sure, why, TimD?  Why the version with the DJ still on it?  Why not one of the recent updates?  Well, some of us like it - the DJ really isn&#039;t that intrusive and I don&#039;t dig editing stuff out of a show.  The sound quality is pretty damn good left alone.  If anyone wants to toy with the show, feel free, but I was very satisfied with it the way I got it, so I&#039;m leaving it alone.

Anyway, real corker of a show - a truly electric Heartbreaker (the first live one?) and a great ICQYB, this show is more or less on par with Dallas 8.31.69 if you added Heartbreaker and rearranged the setlist a little to accommodate it.  A gem, one of the short and sweet treats of 1969 that I love to play in the truck.

Led Zeppelin
1969.10.10
Paris, L&#039;Olympia
Recorded for the show "Musicorama", on french station Europe 1
First broadcast : 1969.11.02
Second Broadcast (not complete) : 2007.11.7
Mono Recording

FM --> MZ RH10 (PCM mode) --> Trader&#039;s Little Helper --> Flac 7

01 - Communication Breakdown
02 - I Can&#039;t Quit You Baby
03 - Heartbreaker
04 - Dazed And Confused
05 - White Summer/Black Mountain Side
06 - You Shook Me
07 - How Many More Times
Moby Dick was played but not broadcasted.
